dataIdInfo.idAbs: This data layer represents roads for Sawyer County, Wisconsin in 2012. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Sawyer_Roads_2012.gdb.[The address range is a linear feature class that contains the high-low, left-right attributes for addresses. This feature class is used for geo coding and may also be used to support dispatching.]
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [The purpose is to support address range management. This feature class may contain actual high and lows as well as theoretical high and lows.]
